list.item:
•Are receiving Hepatitis C drug combinations containing ombitasvir/paritaprevir/ritonavir, with or without dasabuvir, due to the potential for ALT elevations (see 
   Warnings, RISK OF LIVER ENZYME ELEVATIONS WITH CONCOMITANT HEPATITIS C TREATMENT
).

text.paragraph:
During clinical trials with the Hepatitis C combination drug regimen that contains ombitasvir/paritaprevir/ritonavir, with or without dasabuvir, ALT elevations greater than 5 times the upper limit of normal (ULN), including some cases greater than 20 times the ULN, were significantly more frequent in women using ethinyl estradiol-containing medications such as COCs. Discontinue Norethindrone Acetate and Ethinyl Estradiol Tablets, USP and Ferrous Fumarate Tablets prior to starting therapy with the combination drug regimen ombitasvir/paritaprevir/ritonavir, with or without dasabuvir [see 
                              Contraindications (4)
                           ]. Norethindrone Acetate and Ethinyl Estradiol Tablets, USP and Ferrous Fumarate Tablets can be restarted approximately 2 weeks following completion of treatment with the combination drug regimen.
